Sentencas: Herein, we report enhancement of the electrochemical performance of the Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-delta (BSCF/SDC) composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells by improving the ionic conductivity of SDC through addition of CuO.
Titulo: Performance of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-δ-CuO as a cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the effect of the sintering temperature on the crystal structures, surface morphology, and electrochemical properties of the BSCF/SDC-CuO cathode was investigated.
Titulo: Performance of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-δ-CuO as a cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three sintering temperatures were investigated (900, 950, and 1000 degrees C).
Titulo: Performance of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-δ-CuO as a cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The findings showed that raising the SDC ionic conductivity and a sintering temperature of 950 degrees C were the optimal conditions for improving the performance of the composite cathode.
Titulo: Performance of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ/Ce0.85Sm0.15O2-δ-CuO as a cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
